Business Brief -- State Auto Financial Corp.:
   Stake in Pool Arrangement
   Is Raised to 30% From 20%
Under the pooling arrangement, State Auto's largest
subsidiary, State Auto Property  Casualty Insurance Co.,
will receive about $49 million from State Automobile Mutual
to cover its increased share in the pooled liabilities. State
Auto PC will earn investment income on the $49 million as
the liabilities are being settled.
   The arrangement is retroactive to Jan. 1, 1992.
   The two companies have had a pooling arrangement since
1987. It calls for sharing combined premiums, incurred
losses, loss expenses and underwriting expenses.
   In 1991, State Auto Financial earned $1.76 a share, down
from the prior year's $1.44 a share.